 to Vesuvius from a cast of characters as far-flung as Pliny the Younger and Andy Warhol, revealing shifts over time. This cultural and scientific meditation on a powerful natural wonder touches on pagan religious beliefs, vulcanology, and travel writing. Sifting through the ashes of Vesuvius, Darley exposes how changes in our relationship to the volcano mirror changes in our understanding of our cultural and natural environments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aVolcanismxItalyxVesuvius. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2012z978311037491908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067406280140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674062801423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674062801.jpg  a978-3-11-037488-9  HUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014c2011d2014  a978-3-11-037491-9  HUP eBook Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-066256-6  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles